children.subject: I think the 115 before you were all non cs/eecs who didn't fit the reserved seating. But it's great to hear that we have priority on the waitlist as CS majors.

Wait I guess this is a dumb question, but does that mean that as a CS student, even though you're at position 116, if some spots open up, you'll likely get in before other non-CS students who may be earlier on the waitlist? Bc I'm just a couple behind you on the waitlist and really want to get in :/
If the course has reserved seats, then once there's an open reserved seat it would go to the first student on the waitlist who is eligible for that seat.

I believe in this situation a CS major would have priority while the reservation was still active ie. till adjustment period. Once that expires, the only factor that's relevant is your waitlist position, so @anon gear I'd probably treat the situation as if you don't have any sort of priority because I doubt a bunch of people will drop the class before adjustment

I think classes.berkeley.edu is not updated..I am waitlisted for that class at position 116 and I am a CS major (I have no idea why the 115 people before me if were CS majors didn't get into the class), but yes if you are a CS major..you will be prioritized.
